[1] Martinique
Date: Thu 25 Oct 2007
Source: International Herald Tribune, Associated Press report [edited]
<http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2007/10/25/news/CB-GEN-Martinique-Dengue.php>


An elderly man in Martinique has become the 2nd person to die from dengue
fever this year [2007] on the Caribbean island, the health department said
on Thursday [25 Oct 2007].

The victim, who was in his 60s, died at a hospital Tuesday [23 Oct 2007].
He and a man in his 70s who died last month [September 2007] had both
contracted the hemorrhagic form of the mosquitoborne illness, officials said.

Authorities in Martinique, which declared a dengue epidemic in August
[2007], have announced more than 6400 suspected cases on the French
overseas department of about 430 000 people.

