[5] Viet Nam
Date: Thu 25 Oct 2007
Source: Viet Nam News, Nhan Dan (The People) report [edited]
<http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/showarticle.php?num=01DOM251007>


The Ministry of Health has ordered provinces and cities to adopt stringent
measures to prevent and control dengue fever as the risk of new outbreaks
is high in flood-prone areas. Nearly 80 000 cases of mosquitoborne dengue
fever have occurred nationwide this year [2007], 68 of them fatal. The
southern provinces of Dong Thap, Tien Giang, and An Giang continue to lead
the country in the number of cases.

